      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TOO HOT TO TORQUE (4) resumed with the two good trials for a fighting second over 1015m at Ballina. Covered plenty of ground last start and fitter now over his preferred trip. ON MY COMMAND (8) took control from the outset and never headed on debut with a sharp victory over 1100m at this track. Promising type who will relish the extra journey. Go close. KEMAL (7) strengthened over the break and is racing with good consistency. Won well first-up, then warmed up late with a solid second over 1005m at this track. Claim helps and ready for the extra distance. Each way. CRITICAL TIME (5) stalked the speed with the 61kg when he closed late to run second over 1015m at Ballina. Has a good record here and looks close to his top third-up.",
